    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For a truly sophisticated global standard, dress codes must prioritize impeccable fit and fabric over strict uniformity; expect tuxedos in Dubai's evening metrics, bespoke suits in London and NYC, while allowing tailoring degrees for regional heat. Body language should center on controlled presence, avoiding excessive eye contact that might lack interest in some cultures, yet maintaining directness expected in Western boardrooms. Dining etiquette requires mastering complementary gestures like hand movements for bread usage and the importance of the tablecloth, which often acts as a silent translator of success across borders.",
