      "content": "You're absolutely right, and a truly global perspective would invert the perspective, viewing local norms as sophisticated in their own unique ways rather than deviations from a Western ideal. In Tokyo, high-level professional excellence often manifests through hyper-attentive service to guests and implicit respect for hierarchy and silence, rather than loud directness. In Lagos, the standard shifts towards dynamic energy and meaningful face-to-face connection, craving authenticity and inclusivity over rigid formality. By centering your guide on these constituent strengths, you acknowledge that sophistication is defined by cultural competence and adaptability rather than a single, exportable template of suits and gestures.",
